This is my second map, my first being dm_devarena.  This map started as a simple Idea; the four different quadrants of the map would represent four different climate zones, but than I realized, I sucked with displacements.  It was as simple as that, so I put the .vmf aside and went on with my life,  Than I decided to make a new map, dm_devarena,  after completing this map I wanted more and I had remembered that I had a 35% done map just lying in my folders. So I Opened it and began working on it.  I also had optimized many things, I made several pieces of architecture a func_detail to lower compile times, I kept a skybox to a little 2x8 piece in the ceiling at the center.  I also used NoDraw on many of the textures that went unseen, you know the usual mapping stuff.


-This Map Is Completly  Symmetrical (not completly :\ )
-Features many areas for cover and to ambush
-Heavily tested with a team of me and 19 bots
-Supports 20 People
-Not too heavy for snipers with the exception of the outer linings.  
-Probably Best with a shotgun or M4/AK 

*Quick Note* If someone runs a dedicated server and want's to use the map, just give me a quick heads up

dm_crate_liberate is a texture deathmatch map, complete with random spawns. There's a few good camping spots, a few good sniper spots, and a few areas where you don't know what's right around the corner. 

It's meant for 30 players...anymore, and it'd probably be a little too crowded. The map itself isn't that big, and the more people you have the more crazy it'll get. But hey! Crazy can be good sometimes.

Enjoy playing it! I know I enjoyed making it.

- ES: Compre armas y elimine al enemigo.
- EN: Buy weapons and eliminate the enemy.
- Spawns: 40 (20/20).

This is the first map I've made yet. I've received positive feedback from friends so I will post it here. I encourage you to give me any feedback (constructive only, please) that will help me improve this map and my mapping abilities.

a.) Two forts contain spawns for CT and T.
b.) The warehouse is not very well-lit considering budget cuts that result in some failing light fixtures.
c.) There are plenty of crate towers around, some barrels and a catwalk for those who like to be on top.
d.) The terrorist base contains a switch that can turn on/off the lights for some eerie flashlight fun.
e.) The lights are destructible themselves.

Thank you.
Jack Waters

This is a DM map with several different levels to play on. The map itself has 5 different levels.

1. The top level of the map. This is the highest part of the map which also includes the 4 sniper towers on each corner.

2. The Lower top level of the map. This level is probably the most dangerous because people from any lower level can shoot you from that level although the tactical value of this level is very high which makes it worth trying to get to while playing.

3. The mid-level of the map. This area includes the middle shooting windows and the 2 sniper towers by the spawns.

4. The ground level part of the map is where you spawn at and really start off with. From here you can either go up into the higher levels of the map or go down into the lower level.

5. Underground. This level of the map is quite dangerous but can be very strategic if you learn how to use the underground pillars to your advantage. This is an excellent area for close combat.


I tried to make this map so it could fit anyone who plays it. A person who like close combat could easilly go underground to level 5 and play the way they like or go to level 1 and still be able to play there. 

The close combat areas are also excellent for small arms such as pistols and smg's. 

people who like using rifles (non-sniping) could find their home withing levels 2-4. Being that these areas were set up for semi-close combat, using a pistol here (although still deadly) wouldn't be as effective.

Those who like the sniper rifles such as the AWP and the Scout could find their home in the sniper towers which can be accesses through teleporters at the spawn. Although a skilled sniper could easilly go anywhere they want in this map, same goes for any other weapon.


This map is set up for 40 players, has buy zones at spawn, several teleporters, and several lighting effects.
